<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-11-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-11-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="184" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d184">
                        <head><hi rend="italic"><gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                                to Mr. <persName type="to">Schurz</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">[Extract.]</note>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 46.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                    State</hi>,<lb/><placeName><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-11-05"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 5, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of September 2 (No. 13) was
                            duly received.</p>
                        <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>I am gratified to learn that the public opinion around you is less
                            injurious than formerly. I trust that it is the beginning of a better
                            understanding in Europe of the real character and determination of the
                            American people.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer><signed>F. W. SEWARD,</signed><lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting
                                Secretary</hi>.</closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Carl Schurz</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c., Madrid</hi>.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>